        <p class="TableText"><a href="../../../../../Flare/CSH/CSH.htm">Context-sensitive Help (CSH)</a> is a way to tie your existing topics or micro content with specific areas of a software interface. When users click a particular part of the interface (e.g., a Help button), the topic or micro content pertaining to it opens.</p>
        <p class="TableText">If you are creating CSH and need to <a href="../../../../../Flare/CSH/Process/Providing-Developer-Header-File.htm">send the header (.h) file to a developer</a>, Java (.properties) is one of the formats you can use.</p>
    </body>
